ing negative numbers.\n","        Therefore, an alternative way to find the volume at the end of a list/array is:\n","    </p>\n","    <pre>\n","    <code>volume = np.array([20, 19, 18, ..., 10]) </code>\n","    volume[-1]\n","    Output: 10\n","    </pre>\n","</div>\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"LqLqNZfIivEK"},"outputs":[],"source":["# Define the x and y points for the four coordinates\n","# These are for the smallest volume\n","xmin1=\n","xmax1=\n","ymin1=\n","ymax1=\n","\n","#These are for the largest volume\n","xmin2=\n","xmax2=\n","ymin2=\n","ymax2=\n","\n","# Compute the two best fit lines (red and blue lines). Store these as new variables.\n","\n","\n","\n","# Use np.linspace(x_begin, x_end, 100) to create a list of 100 x values to plot between x_begin and x_end\n","V_list=np.linspace()\n","\n","# Calculate the y values using V_list and your new best fit parameters. Store these as new variables.\n","# These lines will represent the red and blue lines as seen above.\n","\n","\n","\n","\n","# Plot the resulting figure using plt.fill_between()\n","# Include the errorbar plot as a base\n","\n","\n","\n","\n","\n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"Ks87NLc5sDdI"},"outputs":[],"source":["# Compute the graphical error as the difference between the slopes or intercepts\n","\n","\n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"F6Qy7LKebijr"},"source":["## 1.8 Calculate V$_\\text{fixed}$\n","\n","<div>\n","  <center> <img height=\"300\" src=\"https://github.com/pmpatel-udallas/CHE-3131/blob/main/Rotation-1-Treatment-of-Data/Figures/Syringe_Vfixed.png?raw=true\"> </center>\n","</div>\n","\n","If we consider that the experimental volume is actually $V_\\text{syringe}$ + $V_\\text{fixed}$, and that the system obeys the ideal gas law, then the following derivation may be used to estimate $V_\\text{fixed}$ from the data. $V_\\text{fixed}$ is the fixed volume of the tubing that connects the syringe to the pressure sensor.\n","$$ p\\times (V_\\text{syringe} + V_\\text{fixed}) = nRT $$\n","$$\\dfrac{1}{p} = \\dfrac{1}{nRT} (V_\\text{syringe} + V_\\text{fixed})$$\n","$$\\dfrac{1}{p} = \\dfrac{1}{nRT}\\times (V_\\text{syringe}) + \\dfrac{V_\\text{fixed}}{nRT}$$\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"cellView":"form","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":73},"id":"3THLFUK_bLmo","outputId":"292d685e-fd9e-4677-dac3-221fb399ee8b"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<IPython.core.display.HTML object>"],"text/html":[" <head>\n","    <!-- See http://docs.mathjax.org/en/latest/web/start.html#using-mathjax-from-a-content-delivery-network-cdn -->\n","    <script type=\"text/javascript\" id=\"MathJax-script\" async\n","        src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mathjax@3/es5/tex-mml-chtml.js\">\n","    </script>\n","</head>\n","\n","<style>\n","div.gold-note {\n","    color: #796748; /* Dark gold for text */\n","    background-color: #F7F0E2; /* Light cream/gold background */\n","    border-left: 5px solid #D8B266; /* Medium gold accent border */\n","    padding: 0.5em;\n","    font-size: 1.25em;\n","    line-height: 1.5;\n","    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n","}\n","</style>\n","\n","<div class=\"gold-note\">\n","\n","    <p>From the information above, how will we calculate \\( V_\\text{fixed} \\)? Provide your answer by writing the appropriate code. </p>\n","</div>\n"]},"metadata":{}}],"source":["# @title **Question 1**\n","%%html\n"," <head>\n","    <!-- See http://docs.mathjax.org/en/latest/web/start.html#using-mathjax-from-a-content-delivery-network-cdn -->\n","    <script type=\"text/javascript\" id=\"MathJax-script\" async\n","        src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mathjax@3/es5/tex-mml-chtml.js\">\n","    </script>\n","</head>\n","\n","<style>\n","div.gold-note {\n","    color: #796748; /* Dark gold for text */\n","    background-color: #F7F0E2; /* Light cream/gold background */\n","    border-left: 5px solid #D8B266; /* Medium gold accent border */\n","    padding: 0.5em;\n","    font-size: 1.25em;\n","    line-height: 1.5;\n","    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n","}\n","</style>\n","\n","<div class=\"gold-note\">\n","\n","    <p>From the information above, how will we calculate \\( V_\\text{fixed} \\)? Provide your answer by writing the appropriate code. </p>\n","</div>\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"AVogVQh3bnzv"},"outputs":[],"source":["# Calculate V_fixed using the results of the best fit lines\n","Vfixed_best=\n","Vfixed_best_err=\n","\n","print('V_fixed using best fit line:', '%0.2f'%Vfixed_best,'±','%0.2f'%Vfixed_best_err)"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"_tkficjDHrST"},"outputs":[],"source":["# Calculate V_fixed using the results of the graphical error determination\n","\n","Vfixed_graph_err=\n","\n","print('V_fixed using best fit line:', '%0.1f'%Vfixed_best,'±','%0.1f'%Vfixed_graph_err)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"pp4924aIqaa7"},"source":["# Part 2. Monte Carlo Sampling\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"cellView":"form","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":280},"id":"sihitAXpi5pR","outputId":"a43ac4bb-4411-4710-d818-c9dc4d26ad0d"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<IPython.core.display.HTML object>"],"text/html":["<style>\n","div.info {\n","    color: #0056b3;\n","    background-color: #d9edf7;\n","    border-left: 5px solid #31708f;\n","    padding: 0.5em;\n","    font-size: 1.25em; /* A little larger the surrounding text size */\n","    line-height: 1.5; /* Ensures readability */\n","}\n","div.info ul {\n","    margin: 0.5em 0; /* Space around the list */\n","}\n","div.info li {\n","    margin-bottom: 0.5em; /* Space between list items */\n","}\n","</style>\n","\n","<div class=\"info\">\n","    <strong>Questions:</strong>\n","    <ul>\n","        <li>How do measurement uncertainties influence the distribution of best-fit lines?</li>\n","        <li>How well does Monte Carlo sampling effectively approximate the error in the slope and intercept?</li>\n","        <li>How do I choose and create the correct plot?</li>\n","        <li>What are different ways to represent experimental uncertainty?</li>\n","    </ul>\n","\n","    <strong>Objectives:</strong>\n","    <ul>\n","        <li>Perform Monte Carlo sampling of error uncertainty.</li>\n","    </ul>\n","</div>\n"]},"metadata":{}}],"source":["# @title Overview\n","%%html\n","<style>\n","div.info {\n","    color: #0056b3;\n","    background-color: #d9edf7;\n","    border-left: 5px solid #31708f;\n","    padding: 0.5em;\n","    font-size: 1.25em; /* A little larger the surrounding text size */\n","    line-height: 1.5; /* Ensures readability */\n","}\n","div.info ul {\n","    margin: 0.5em 0; /* Space around the list */\n","}\n","div.info li {\n","    margin-bottom: 0.5em; /* Space between list items */\n","}\n","</style>\n","\n","<div class=\"info\">\n","    <strong>Questions:</strong>\n","    <ul>\n","        <li>How do measurement uncertainties influence the distribution of best-fit lines?</li>\n","        <li>How well does Monte Carlo sampling effectively approximate the error in the slope and intercept?</li>\n","        <li>How do I choose and create the correct plot?</li>\n","        <li>What are different ways to represent experimental uncertainty?</li>\n","    </ul>\n","\n","    <strong>Objectives:</strong>\n","    <ul>\n","        <li>Perform Monte Carlo sampling of error uncertainty.</li>\n","    </ul>\n","</div>"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"nmOZZiiIjhUy"},"source":["**Monte Carlo** algorithms are a class of computational methods that use repeated random sampling to obtain numerical results. These methods are especially useful for solving problems that are difficult or impossible to address analytically, such as evaluating multi-dimensional integrals, modeling uncertainty, or simulating physical systems with complex behavior. By generating a large number of random inputs, Monte Carlo simulations can be used to approximate outcomes, calculate probabilities, or explore the statistical properties of a system."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## 2.1 Demonstration"],"metadata":{"id":"5IG_XY5FMPeu"}},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"cellView":"form","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":99},"id":"ArdRFzmfjuhJ","outputId":"d9a1125f-a5d3-4391-b3fa-3a6aaab54b57"},"outputs":[{"data":{"text/html":[" <head>\n","    <!-- See http://docs.mathjax.org/en/latest/web/start.html#using-mathjax-from-a-content-delivery-network-cdn -->\n","    <script type=\"text/javascript\" id=\"MathJax-script\" async\n","        src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mathjax@3/es5/tex-mml-chtml.js\">\n","    </script>\n","  </head>\n","\n","\n","<style>\n","div.orange-alert {\n","    color: #854f00; /* Darker shade of orange for text */\n","    background-color: #ffe6cc; /* Light orange background */\n","    border-left: 5px solid #ff9933; /* Bright orange border */\n","    padding: 0.5em;\n","    font-size: 1.25em; /* Matches the surrounding text size */\n","    line-height: 1.5; /* Ensures readability */\n","}\n","div.orange-alert ul {\n","    margin: 0.5em 0; /* Space around the list */\n","}\n","div.orange-alert li {\n","    margin-bottom: 0.5em; /* Space between list items */\n","}\n","</style>\n","<div class=\"orange-alert\">\n","    <p>Run the code cell below to estimate \\( \\pi \\) using a Monte Carlo sampling of the ratio\n","      between the number of points that lie within a circle and within a square of unit distance (\\(r=1\\))\n","    </p>\n","\n","</div>\n"],"text/plain":["<IPython.core.display.HTML object>"]},"metadata":{},"output_type":"display_data"}],"source":["# @title Exercise: Estimate $\\pi$\n","%%html\n"," <head>\n","    <!-- See http://docs.mathjax.org/en/latest/web/start.html#using-mathjax-from-a-content-delivery-network-cdn -->\n","    <script type=\"text/javascript\" id=\"MathJax-script\" async\n","        src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mathjax@3/es5/tex-mml-chtml.js\">\n","    </script>\n","  </head>\n","\n","\n","<style>\n","div.orange-alert {\n","    color: #854f00; /* Darker shade of orange for text */\n","    background-color: #ffe6cc; /* Light orange background */\n","    border-left: 5px solid #ff9933; /* Bright orange border */\n","    padding: 0.5em;\n","    font-size: 1.25em; /* Matches the surrounding text size */\n","    line-height: 1.5; /* Ensures readability */\n","}\n","div.orange-alert ul {\n","    margin: 0.5em 0; /* Space around the list */\n","}\n","div.orange-alert li {\n","    margin-bottom: 0.5em; /* Space between list items */\n","}\n","</style>\n","<div class=\"orange-alert\">\n","    <p>Run the code cell below to estimate \\( \\pi \\) using a Monte Carlo sampling of the ratio\n","      between the number of points that lie within a circle and within a square of unit distance (\\(r=1\\))\n","    </p>\n","</div>\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"G7E06iyjqk57"},"source":["For a distance $r$, since\n","$$A_{circle}=\\pi r^2$$\n","$$A_{square} = 4r^2$$\n","\n","then,\n","$$ 4 * \\dfrac{A_{circle}}{A_{square}} = 4 * \\dfrac{\\pi r^2}{4r^2} = \\pi $$"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"GZFeClkBqZLk"},"outputs":[],"source":["# Define the number of points in a circle and square\n","circle_points = 0\n","square_points = 0\n","\n","# Define the intervals\n","INTERVAL=[1e2+1, 1e3+1, 1e4+1, 1e5+1, 1e6+1, 1e7+1, 2e7+1]\n","\n","# Drawing the circle\n","Xspace = np.linspace(-1,1,20001)\n","Yspace = np.sqrt(1-Xspace**2)\n","\n","# Run a loop over all possible values\n","for i in trange(len(INTERVAL)):\n","    #Generate the number of sampling points\n","    rand_x = np.random.uniform(-1,1,int(INTERVAL[i]))\n","    rand_y = np.random.uniform(-1,1,int(INTERVAL[i]))\n","\n","    # Calculate the distance of (x,y) to origin\n","    origin_dist = rand_x**2 + rand_y**2\n","\n","    # Checking if (x,y) lies within the circle using the np.where() function, which returns elements\n","    cond = np.where(origin_dist<=1)\n","    cond2= np.array(sorted(list(set(np.arange(INTERVAL[i],dtype=int))-set(cond[0]))))\n","\n","    # Computing the number of points inside the circle\n","    circle_points = len(cond[0])\n","\n","    #Computing the number of points inside the square (includes inside the circle) -- all the points\n","    square_points = INTERVAL[i]\n","\n","    # Plot the circle points and square points\n","    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(5,5))\n","    plt.plot(rand_x[cond],rand_y[cond],'o',markersize=0.75,color='#1A3F70')\n","    plt.plot(rand_x[cond2],rand_y[cond2],'o',markersize=0.75,color='#D8B266')\n","    plt.plot(Xspace,Yspace,'k')\n","    plt.plot(Xspace,-Yspace,'k')\n","    plt.show()\n","\n","    # Estimate pi from Monte Carlo simulations\n","    pi_est = 4 * circle_points/square_points\n","    print('Estimate of pi using '+str(int(INTERVAL[i]))+' points:','%0.6f'%pi_est)\n","    error=np.abs(np.pi-pi_est)\n","    print('Error Estimate of pi using '+str(int(INTERVAL[i]))+' points:','%0.6f'%error)\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"cellView":"form","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":73},"id":"gPkgqI1IWl3-","outputId":"803a20bb-4c0a-4f27-e107-ce1f5717c210"},"outputs":[{"data":{"text/html":["<style>\n","div.gold-note {\n","    color: #796748; /* Dark gold for text */\n","    background-color: #F7F0E2; /* Light cream/gold background */\n","    border-left: 5px solid #D8B266; /* Medium gold accent border */\n","    padding: 0.5em;\n","    font-size: 1.25em;\n","    line-height: 1.5;\n","    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n","}\n","</style>\n","\n","<div class=\"gold-note\">\n"," \n","    <p>Discuss as a group what you think was happening in this demonstration? Include your answer below.</p>\n","</div>\n"],"text/plain":["<IPython.core.