td, sum, etc.). For example,\n","```python\n","df.mean()\n","```\n","In the parentheses part of the operation, there are two main options.\n","\n","```python\n","axis=0 # Operations along the column\n","axis=1 # Operations along the row\n","```"],"metadata":{"id":"9MtrG1zwcDEa"}},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"cellView":"form","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":216},"id":"gdgyUkZYphs4","outputId":"e7de831a-e846-4813-c38a-353bf26218fd"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<IPython.core.display.HTML object>"],"text/html":["<style>\n","div.orange-alert {\n","    color: #854f00; /* Darker shade of orange for text */\n","    background-color: #ffe6cc; /* Light orange background */\n","    border-left: 5px solid #ff9933; /* Bright orange border */\n","    padding: 0.5em;\n","    font-size: 1.25em; /* Matches the surrounding text size */\n","    line-height: 1.5; /* Ensures readability */\n","}\n","div.orange-alert ul {\n","    margin: 0.5em 0; /* Space around the list */\n","}\n","div.orange-alert li {\n","    margin-bottom: 0.5em; /* Space between list items */\n","}\n","</style>\n","<div class=\"orange-alert\">\n","    <p>Calculate the mean and standard deviation by doing the following:\n","    <ul>\n","      <li>Import the sample data for Option 2 using <code>pd.read_excel()</code>\n","      to a variable named sample_data</li>\n","      <li>Calculate the mean using the mean function (<code>sample_data.mean()</code>).</li>\n","      <ul>\n","        <li> Use the <code>axis=0</code> and <code>axis=1</code> options (<code>sample_data.mean(axis=0)</code>)\n","      </ul>\n","    <li> Use the standard deviation function (<code>sample_data.std()</code>)</li>\n","    </ul>\n","    </p>\n","</div>\n"]},"metadata":{}}],"source":["# @title Exercise: axis=0 vs. axis=1\n","%%html\n","<style>\n","div.orange-alert {\n","    color: #854f00; /* Darker shade of orange for text */\n","    background-color: #ffe6cc; /* Light orange background */\n","    border-left: 5px solid #ff9933; /* Bright orange border */\n","    padding: 0.5em;\n","    font-size: 1.25em; /* Matches the surrounding text size */\n","    line-height: 1.5; /* Ensures readability */\n","}\n","div.orange-alert ul {\n","    margin: 0.5em 0; /* Space around the list */\n","}\n","div.orange-alert li {\n","    margin-bottom: 0.5em; /* Space between list items */\n","}\n","</style>\n","<div class=\"orange-alert\">\n","    <p>Calculate the mean and standard deviation by doing the following:\n","    <ul>\n","      <li>Import the sample data for Option 2 using <code>pd.read_excel()</code>\n","      to a variable named sample_data</li>\n","      <li>Calculate the mean using the mean function (<code>sample_data.mean()</code>).</li>\n","      <ul>\n","        <li> Use the <code>axis=0</code> and <code>axis=1</code> options (<code>sample_data.mean(axis=0)</code>)\n","      </ul>\n","    <li> Use the standard deviation function (<code>sample_data.std()</code>)</li>\n","    </ul>\n","    </p>\n","</div>"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"QbATVY6srniY","scrolled":true},"outputs":[],"source":["# Import sample data here\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"ofOw8gkXtySs"},"outputs":[],"source":["# Calculate the mean of sample_data along axis 0\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"qQ54JC0FuinN"},"outputs":[],"source":["# Calculate the mean of sample_data along axis 1\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"cellView":"form","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":162},"id":"SIKMJtdsne0b","outputId":"9a66b4ee-48f6-4f6f-8b96-72a270de5d67"},"outputs":[{"data":{"text/html":["<div id=\"xnxbpagiQFrS\" data-shufflequestions=\"False\" data-shuffleanswers=\"True\" data-preserveresponses=\"false\" data-numquestions=\"1000000\" data-maxwidth=\"600\" style=\"border-radius: 10px; text-align: left\"><style>\n","#xnxbpagi